---
title: `$path::B()`
description: Convert file path to its base name.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Path::B($path, $step = 1, $s = null);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$test_1 = Path::B('foo\bar\baz.qux');
$test_2 = Path::B('foo\bar\baz.qux', 2);
$test_3 = Path::B('foo-bar-baz.qux', 1, '-');
$test_4 = Path::B('foo.bar.baz.qux', 1, '.');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test_1 = 'baz.qux';
$test_2 = 'bar\baz.qux';
$test_3 = 'baz.qux';
$test_4 = 'qux';
~~~